Package ePortfolio

Class Portfolio

  • java.lang.Object
    • ePortfolio.Portfolio
  • public class Portfolio
extends java.lang.Object
    Portfolio class responsible for keeping records of different type of investments into an ArrayList. Records can be saved and loaded from files and investments can be searched for based on user criteria.

      • buy

        public java.lang.String buy​(java.lang.String type,
                            java.lang.String symbol,
                            java.lang.String name,
                            java.lang.String quantity,
                            java.lang.String price)
                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Method performs a purchase operation on the calling Portfolio object. A new Stock or MutualFund is added to the ArrayLists if the investment didn't previously exist. Quantity, price and bookvalue are updated for ane existing investment object with a matching symbol.
        Parameters:
        type - String object containing the type for investment to be purchased
        name - String object containing the name for investment to be purchased
        symbol - String object containing the symbol for investment to be purchased
        quantity - String object containing the integer quantity value for investment to be purchased
        price - String object containing the double price value for investment to be purchased
        Returns:
        String object containing the purchased investment information.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • sell

        public java.lang.String sell​(java.lang.String symbol,
                             java.lang.String quantity,
                             java.lang.String price)
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        Method performs a sell operation on the calling Portfolio object. Stock or MutualFund is removed from the ArrayLists if the quantity reaches 0. Error Exception generated when investment doesn't exist in Portfolio object.
        Parameters:
        symbol - String object containing the symbol for investment to be sold
        quantity - String object containing the integer quantity value for investment to be sold
        price - String object containing the double price value for investment to be sold
        Returns:
        String object containing the transaction information.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • search

        public java.lang.String search​(java.lang.String symbol,
                               java.lang.String keywords,
                               java.lang.String lowerPrice,
                               java.lang.String higherPrice)
                        throws java.lang.Exception
        Method searches for investments based on user defined criteria. User is prompted for search criteria (symbol, name keywords and price range). The user can skip any of the fields during entry. Method then outputs all Stock and MutualFund objects that match the criteria to the screen.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • investmentExists

        public int investmentExists​(java.util.ArrayList<Investment> investments,
                            java.lang.String symbol)
        Method searches for an Investment object in ArrayList of investment objects. The symbol is the used criteria to find the desired object.
        Parameters:
        investments - An ArrayList of Investment objects to be searched.
        symbol - A String object containing the symbol used as criteria for the search algorithm.
        Returns:
        An integer value containing the index of the Investment object in the ArrayList if found. -1 is returned otherwise.
